evaluation.response:
It sounds like you're facing a tough situation, and it's completely understandable to feel a bit lost and anxious.

First, prioritize your health and well-being. Rest and recovery are just as important as practice and competition. When you're injure, your body is trying to heal, and putting excessive strain on it can end up causing even more harm.&#x20;

As for race week, it’s okay to celebrate and enjoy meals off your strict plan. To stay prepped you can look over the menu beforehand and see what sounds the least heavy. Or you could make a small meal at home anyway that fits your plan on race day as the last thing we need is an intense calorie crash.&#x20;

If you're feeling overwhelmed, make sure to seek support from your loved ones and mental health professionals if necessary. Hang in there! These feelings are temporary and with the right support, you'll get through this and come out stronger.
